notesStmt.note: Title supplied by cataloger (Zacour-Hirsch). Title on cover partly missing due to damage to parchment.
Compiled on the orders of Antonio Giuseppe Affarosi, lord of the town, "noble of Reggio" [Calabria? Emilia?] (note, f. 2v).

msContents.summary: Deliberations of meetings of the town council ("consilium generale hominum communitas jurisdictionis Sancti Bartholomei in Saxo Forte") from 1718-1783.

supportDesc.extent: 134 leaves : 367 x 240 mm. bound to 374 x 235 mm. +
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 134; [1-134]; modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in various cursive scripts by multiple hands.

decoDesc.decoNote: Illustrated with coat of arms of Antonius de Affarusii in watercolor (f. 1r). Entries stamped with notarial seals throughout.
